  "prompt": "How do you know when you are going into the friendzone?",
  "response": "Here are some signs you might be heading into the friendzone:\n\n1. Physical/Romantic Signals\n- They only talk to you platonically\n- No physical flirting or touching\n- They never show romantic interest\n- They see you as a \"good friend\"\n\n2. Conversation Dynamics\n- They discuss their romantic interests with you\n- Always refer to you as \"buddy\" or \"like a brother/sister\"\n- They don't get jealous when you talk about other potential partners\n\n3. Interaction Patterns\n- They're comfortable around you but don't show attraction\n- They're happy to hang out, but always in group settings\n- They seek your advice about other romantic prospects\n- They treat you more like a confidant than a potential partner\n\n4. Body Language\n- No romantic eye contact\n- No subtle physical closeness\n- Lack of romantic tension\n- Purely friendly/casual interactions\n\n5. Dating Behavior\n- They never suggest one-on-one romantic dates\n- Always suggest group activities\n- Never initiate romantic or intimate conversations\n\nPrevention Tips:\n- Show clear romantic interest early\n- Flirt subtly\n- Maintain some mystery\n- Be confident\n- Express your feelings directly\n\nRemember, every situation is unique, and communication is key.",
